HEADWORD: Inexpiate
<hw>In*ex"pi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexpiatus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Expiate</er>.]</ety> <def>Not appeased or placated.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To rest <qex>inexpiate</qex> were much too rude a part.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexplainable</ent>⟦br⟧
